      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The economic impact of unions is a complex debate with differing viewpoints. Proponents argue that unions raise wages and improve working conditions, which can boost consumer spending and reduce inequality, benefiting the economy. Critics, however, contend that higher labor costs can drive up prices for consumers and reduce business competitiveness. Ultimately, the effect often depends on the specific industry, the strength of the union, and broader economic conditions.",
