      "role": "user",
      "content": "it just seems like a lot of the talking points about them \"raising wages\" are really just a way to justify more regulation and higher taxes. if you look at the actual data, doesn't it show that most of the progress in worker rights actually came from general economic growth rather than unions forcing it?",
